This is an addition to the existing imports. The file currently imports from `node:fs/promises` and `node:path` but does not import `constants`.

**Updated `validateSkillContract`:**

```typescript
async function validateSkillContract(
  source: string,
  skillPath: string,
): Promise<void> {
  let stat: import("node:fs").Stats;
  try {
    stat = await lstat(source);
  } catch (err) {
    const code = (err as NodeJS.ErrnoException).code;
    if (code === "ENOENT") {
      throw new UserError(
        "DEPLOY_FAILED",
        `Skill "${skillPath}" source not found: ${source}`,
      );
    }
    if (code === "EACCES" || code === "EPERM") {
      throw new UserError(
        "DEPLOY_FAILED",
        `Permission denied accessing skill "${skillPath}" source: ${source}`,
      );
    }
    throw new UserError(
      "DEPLOY_FAILED",
      `Cannot access skill "${skillPath}" source: ${source}`,
    );
  }
  if (!stat.isDirectory()) {
    throw new UserError(
      "DEPLOY_FAILED",
      `Skill "${skillPath}" source is not a directory: ${source}`,
    );
  }
  // Check that the skill directory itself is readable (not just accessible via lstat)
  try {
    await access(source, constants.R_OK);
  } catch (err) {
    const code = (err as NodeJS.ErrnoException).code;
    if (code === "EACCES" || code === "EPERM") {
      throw new UserError(
        "DEPLOY_FAILED",
        `Permission denied reading skill directory "${skillPath}": ${source}`,
      );
    }
    throw new UserError(
      "DEPLOY_FAILED",
      `Cannot read skill directory "${skillPath}": ${source}`,
    );
  }
  // Check for SKILL.md, distinguishing missing vs not readable
  try {
    await access(path.join(source, "SKILL.md"), constants.R_OK);
  } catch (err) {
    const code = (err as NodeJS.ErrnoException).code;
    if (code === "ENOENT") {
      throw new UserError(
        "DEPLOY_FAILED",
        `Skill "${skillPath}" source is missing SKILL.md: ${source}`,
      );
    }
    if (code === "EACCES" || code === "EPERM") {
      throw new UserError(
        "DEPLOY_FAILED",
        `Permission denied reading SKILL.md in skill "${skillPath}": ${source}`,
      );
    }
    throw new UserError(
      "DEPLOY_FAILED",
      `Cannot access SKILL.md in skill "${skillPath}": ${source}`,
    );
  }
}
```

**Note on `access` call:** The original code calls `await access(path.join(source, "SKILL.md"))` without a mode flag, defaulting to `constants.F_OK` (existence only). The new code uses `constants.R_OK` for readability. This is semantically correct — we want to know whether the file is readable, not just that it exists. The same applies to the directory readability check.

**Why the directory R_OK check is needed:** After `lstat` succeeds and `isDirectory()` passes, we know the directory entry exists and is a directory, but we do not yet know whether we can read its contents. A directory can have `--x` (execute-only) permission — we can `lstat` it (because we have parent directory traverse) but `cp` or `readdir` will fail with EACCES. Adding `access(source, R_OK)` catches this before attempting deployment.

